The paper discusses the implementation of a specialized hardware architecture for CapsuleNets, which are a type of neural network used for image recognition and computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CV (Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of matrix computations and routing algorithms, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
